Manchester United have been handed a major boost ahead of their Premier League clash with Arsenal on Monday night. Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s side could feature forward, Anthony Martial when they take on Arsenal at Old Trafford. Martial has been out of action for Solskjaer’s men with a thigh injury since Man United’s 2-1 defeat to Crystal Palace at the end of last month. Anthony Martial is set to return in time for Manchester United’s clash with Arsenal, according to reports. According to Evening Standard, the France international has returned to Man United’s training ahead of their Premier League clash against the Gunners. The newspaper added that the 23-year-old is in contention to feature for the Red Devils against Unai Emery’s side on Monday. Man United head to the game following a 2-0 defeat to West Ham United in their last encounter. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.